The joystick class is based on interfacing with an xbox controller using the xboxdrv driver.

To install the xboxdrv driver:
$ sudo apt-get install xboxdrv

run the driver:
$ sudo xboxdrv

xboxdrv links:
git repository - https://github.com/xboxdrv/xboxdrv
manual page - http://pingus.seul.org/~grumbel/xboxdrv/

coding references:
simple joystick program - https://gist.github.com/jasonwhite/c5b2048c15993d285130
file decriptors - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File_descriptor
gnu C library - http://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/index.html#SEC_Contents
cancellation points - http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/xsh_chap02_09.html
makefiles - http://mrbook.org/blog/tutorials/make/
	  - https://www.gnu.org/software/make/manual/make.html
	  - http://www.tutorialspoint.com/makefile/ (GOOD)

timers 
timer with callback examples - http://stackoverflow.com/questions/19022320/implementing-timer-with-timeout-handler-in-c
      	   	    	     - http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14650885/how-to-create-timer-events-using-c-11
time in c++ - http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/chrono/c/time

-----compiling xboxdrv from source-----
following instructions at https://github.com/xboxdrv/xboxdrv

apt-get install python{,3}-pip
pip install python-uinput
apt-get install g++ libusb-1.0-0 pkg-config libudev-dev libboost-dev scons libX11-dev libdbus-1-dev glibc-source

then continue with online instructions